<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1058,899,951]" pageId="33" pageNumber="1178">
E t y m o l o g y: Thetrivialname, 
<emphasis box="[532,615,899,920]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="1178">gibberis</emphasis>
, is a Latin adjective that stems from 
<emphasis box="[992,1058,899,920]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="1178">gibber</emphasis>
(= swollen). I refer to the swollen condition of the basal 1/4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[755,767,925,939]" fontSize="6" pageId="33" pageNumber="1178">th</superScript>
of the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
